<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 99-12-04 - Engine Front Cover</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi991204" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>99-12-04</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>February, 1999</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Engine Front Cover</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>DT 408</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 466</engfam>
                <engfam>International&#174; 530</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 466E</engfam>
                <engfam>International&#174; 530E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>FRONT COVER INSPECTION</title>
                <para>When an engine water pump bearing failure occurs, the rear half of the engine front cover may
                    sustain damage in the area behind the pump impeller.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>To determine if the rear half of the front cover is reusable, the following procedure can be used.
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Measure deepest groove in damaged area with a caliper or depth micrometer. Typically, the
                        outer region of the grooved damaged area is where gouging is the deepest. Refer to Figure 1
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f99120401">Front Cover Inspection
                            <xref refid="f99120401"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        .
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Maximum allowable depth of damaged area may not exceed .120 inches (3.048 mm).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If front cover damage does not exceed .120 inches (3.048 mm), the front cover can be reused
                        and cooling system pressures and flow will not be negatively affected.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="f99120401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/EG8013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="144"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Front Cover Inspection</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
